MW14 have also considered the single-Fisher model, and the addition of the asteroseismic sample in the present analysis leads to consistent results within the quoted credible regions. For multi-transiting systems, however, the posteriors of $\kappa$ in both works differ in shape and appear to be dominated at large $\kappa$ by their respective priors. Our choice of a uniform prior on $\kappa$, as opposed to $p(\kappa)\!\propto\!(1+\kappa^2)^{-3/4}$ in MW14, was made to prevent the underestimation of $\kappa$ when $\kappa$ is large. We confirmed our suspicion that the prior may be dominating at large $\kappa$ by repeating the analysis having used the latter prior on $\kappa$ instead. We take this as an indication that the available data may not be able to fully constrain the posterior of $\kappa$ for multi-transiting systems, in particular at large $\kappa$.

