As a further sanity check, detailed peak-bagging was conducted for all stars using an affine-invariant ensemble MCMC algorithm \citep{emcee,Lund14}. The main purpose of this exercise was to both investigate the impact of the sampling algorithm on the resulting joint PPD and the impact of using a different frequency range (or number of observed modes) in the peak-bagging analysis. The overall agreement between the Metropolis--Hastings (on which our results are based; see Appendix \ref{append:specfit}) and affine-invariant implementations is excellent.

